                },
                {
                    "text": " at the county fair and won first prize for her chocolate cake"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Skill-based = contest/competition. Luck-based = sweepstakes/lottery. Scammers often claim you 'won' a contest you never entered — a major red flag!"
        },
        {
            "word": "member",
            "wordType": "noun",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "A person who belongs to a group, organization, club, or association and typically pays "
                },
                {
                    "text": "fees for access",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " to "
                },
                {
                    "text": "benefits or services",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "عضو",
            "synonyms": [
                "participant",
                "affiliate",
                "subscriber"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "As a library "
                },
                {
                    "text": "member",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": ", you can borrow up to twenty books at a time and access online research databases for free"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Pattern: member OF something ('member of the club'). Not the same as 'customer' (buys goods/services) vs. 'member' (belongs to an organization)."
